							<o:Column Id="o768">
								<a:ObjectID>8C6B7729-17FB-4197-8702-127C065D8AB2</a:ObjectID>
								<a:Name>Sector of activity</a:Name>
								<a:Code>FACACTSCT_CT</a:Code>
								<a:CreationDate>860680380</a:CreationDate>
								<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
								<a:ModificationDate>860680380</a:ModificationDate>
								<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
								<a:Comment>Sector of activity</a:Comment>
								<a:DefaultValue>999</a:DefaultValue>
								<a:DataType>int</a:DataType>
								<a:Mandatory>1</a:Mandatory>
								<a:Annotation>The activity sector belong to Client Segmentation table (BCLI..TREPCRI) and a segment equals to his group segment : possible values = lines of TREPCRI with HORDNBR_NT (segment code) = HORDGRP_NT (sector code).  His FAC definition is:  fac sector activity is initialised  during the link with fac main policyholder : it takes the value of corresponding client sector to main policyholder. The way is : TCONTR --- (pcpind_nf = ind_nf) -- TINSURED -- (cliind_nf = cli_nf) -- TCLIENT -- (Cli_nf = cli_nf and cliresssd_cf = ssd_cf) -- TCLREPCR -- (hordnbr_nt, lag_cf) TREPCRI  You can modified it after. For S/R, it's  FACACTSCT_CT of TCONTR.</a:Annotation>
							</o:Column>
