					<o:Table Id="o234">
						<a:ObjectID>35AA1E4D-417A-4F91-A332-59C74D9AB995</a:ObjectID>
						<a:Name>Zoom on claims</a:Name>
						<a:Code>TZOOCLM</a:Code>
						<a:CreationDate>860680380</a:CreationDate>
						<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
						<a:ModificationDate>1029749440</a:ModificationDate>
						<a:Modifier>FRICJY</a:Modifier>
						<a:Comment>Zoom on claims</a:Comment>
						<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
						<a:Annotation>That table serve to support of claim zoom windows, open from windows presenting fac accumulation statistic. It is erased and filled in monthly in edition batch of the activity report and accumulation statistic of facs . Activity datas are linked to fac claims, new or modified during the month, treatied fac into TFACACT, and only claims which have the total (paid claim + SAP+ ACR) is superior to minimum threshold describe in TPARAM. Statistic datas are linked to fac claims used in TFACSTA, and only claims which the total (paid claims + SA + ACR) is superior to minimum threshold describe in TPARAM. Their volume is estimated to 20000lines for Europe site. </a:Annotation>
						<c:Columns>
							<o:Column Id="o960">
								<a:ObjectID>7DBC77CB-AEA9-4C59-AAF3-3E87B5734D95</a:ObjectID>
								<a:Name>Zoom on claims number</a:Name>
								<a:Code>ZOOCLM_NT</a:Code>
								<a:CreationDate>860680380</a:CreationDate>
								<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
								<a:ModificationDate>860680380</a:ModificationDate>
								<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
								<a:Comment>Zoom on claims number</a:Comment>
								<a:DataType>numeric(10)</a:DataType>
								<a:Length>10</a:Length>
								<a:Identity>1</a:Identity>
								<a:Mandatory>1</a:Mandatory>
							</o:Column>
							<o:Column Id="o961">
								<a:ObjectID>7ABAE4BD-C871-471B-9600-02B800C279F5</a:ObjectID>
								<a:Name>Data type</a:Name>
								<a:Code>DATTYP_CT</a:Code>
								<a:CreationDate>860680380</a:CreationDate>
								<a:Creator>OME08</a:Creator>
								<a:ModificationDate>860680380</a:ModificationDate>
								<a:Modifier>OME08</a:Modifier>
								<a:Comment>Data type</a:Comment>
								<a:DefaultValue>''</a:DefaultValue>
								<a:DataType>char(3)</a:DataType>
								<a:Length>3</a:Length>
								<a:Mandatory>1</a:Mandatory>
								<a:DistinctValues>0</a:DistinctValues>
								<a:Annotation>That column take the value "ACT" when we concentrated on fac activity; or the value " STA" when we concentrated on fac accumulation statistic</a:Annotation>
